"reviewcomment":"The food here was amazing and didn&#39;t disappoint!  There were lots of spicy and interesting flavors which made for some memorable bites.  <br><br>We got the tasting menu and started with barbequed squid with Thai basil and peanuts (one of my favorite dishes) which was my favorite dish of the night.  <br><br>This was followed by the soup dumpling topped with seared foie gras which was also very good but I had issues with eating it.  Too big to pop in my mouth but when I bite into it hotness spills out burning my mouth!  <br><br>The entree dishes were Spanish mackerel with a Korean chili sauce (another favorite) and lamb with chickpeas, harissa, and black sesame.  The mackerel dish was amazing (almost tying with the barbequed squid) but the lamb dish was just pretty good.  Not as amazing as the other dishes.<br><br>Finally, my friends and I shared the three different desserts of poppy seed bread and butter pudding with meyer lemon curd, strawberry parfait with tofu, and pecan and Salted butterscotch beignets with bourbon milk ice.  All very yummy and I had no favorites among the three.  <br><br>All in all a great dining experience and will eagerly return the next time I&#39;m back in NY!",
