"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Once upon a time, there was a majestic city.<br>And a vast green park lay in a heart of it. Brightly decorated horse equipages carried fancy-dressed ladies and gentlemen along the road that encircled it. And on the other side of the road was a beautiful place called Marea.<br>...but this once upon a time is Now. and Here. <br><br>It&#39;s a classy place. The view of Central Park is wonderful. Servers are courteous. Table cloth are sharp, and table decorations are romantic.<br><br>Pre-fix menus are great since you can pretty much select everything. And while crudi did not impress me much (they were fresh, but rather ordinary), the main dish was outstanding. It was strozzapreti, with crab meat &amp; sea urchin. Pasta was handmade, perfectly cooked and flavors worked perfectly together.<br><br>Now, what I want to really rave about, are their drinks. Yes, they are pricey. But soooo well-crafted. I was celebrating after all, and being big fan of Remi, I had to get XO Sidecar, of course. It was nothing short of fantastic. <br><br>One last thing to finish great meal - mascarpone panna cotta. It was a masterpiece, served with granita on top, very refreshing and smooth at same time.<br><br>Yes, I will be coming back for the bar and desserts. Absolutely.",
