"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Gilt was amazing!!! We came here for our anniversary back in October 2012. It&#39;s a nice huge restaurant inside the Palace Hotel and you walk into the garden of the hotel and it&#39;s on the right hand side. It&#39;s beautiful. Nice tall ceilings and great service from the moment you walk in. They took our coats and seated us promptly since we had reservations. We came here for our anniversary. This is definitely a once in a lifetime experience! I mean our bill came out to maybe $500 for 2 people for the 7-course meal and alcohol! It&#39;s crazy and definitely the most we have paid for dinner. Also, he had arranged for them to set up a bouquet of flowers on the table and it looked amazing! :)<br><br>As for the food, we decided to go for the $150 7-course tasting menu. In comparison to the 5-course that is $120, and the 3-course meal for $89, it seemed like a better deal. Plus, it was a special occasion and our first time here so we decided to go all out. Our waiter was amazing and very attentive. In addition, there&#39;s a water guy, and a bread guy. It&#39;s so funny that they come around filling up our water so often and they come and ask us which kind of bread we want and you can choose as many options as you wanted. When I only asked for one, he&#39;s like which other ones would you like? I&#39;m like ohhhh...lol.<br><br>Anyways, for the entire night, it felt like the food just kept coming and coming and coming and I think it felt way more than a 7-course tasting menu. There were appetizers, entrees, and desserts. And we were wondering when it would end because it must be the longest dinner I have ever had, maybe 2-3 hours long...LOL! All the food and arrangements were very interesting and delicious. However, I can say that some of the food was a little bit too salty.<br><br>At the end of the night, they gave us a nice dessert plate written &#34;Happy Anniversary&#34; on it. Awesome! :)",
