"reviewcomment":"I came here for a date night and I was told this was a nice little sushi spot. Honestly just from walking in. I thought that, that was an understatement. The decor is seriously sooo nice. In the words of another woman sitting next to me, it feels like we&#39;re sitting in a jewelry box. Except it&#39;s not all razzle dazzle rather bamboo-ish. Right away I was surprisingly pleased at the good service provided. <br><br>We ordered literally salmon on, in, under EVERYTHING. We requested three different types of salmon sashimi and it was just sooo tender, fresh and i swear it melted in my mouth. That should do it for the rest of the salmon we ordered as well. The tartar with the different types of fishes were yummy too with the sweet potato chips. <br><br>For dessert we had the Green tea sandwiches and Tiramisu which was also really yummy but I was so full I couldn&#39;t enjoy it as much as if I had the room for it. We were also rushing it because we had a play to attend to right after. Even with the amount of food we ordered we both thought it was actually priced fairly. <br><br>Would I come back here? Yes! and I would highly recommend this to anyone who loves Sashimi.",
