"reviewcomment":"Not bad. It&#39;s a little cramped by the window. I had a tough time getting in my seat. The couple next to us was sort of loud and kept making a fuss with the waiters. One time they had this empty bowl with sauce in it and they yelled at the waiter when he tried to take it away. Crazy. <br><br>Anyways... the service could be better. We had to wait like 3 minutes after we were seated to look at a menu even though I saw one waiter just standing around. I came here with restaurant week with my girlfriend but I&#39;ll come back again.<br><br>We ordered the crispy pig ears. Not a bad dish. Came with small apple slices. The pig ears came out a bit too dry.<br><br>As for our restaurant week menu choices, the pulpo was delicious. Perfectly cooked. Sort of seemed like they boiled it first before grilling them slightly to get that sick Maillard reaction. <br><br>Girlfriend got Tortilla with Romesco and Jamón Serrano, the Jamon was the usual but the tortilla was more like a layered potato cake. It was done very well.<br><br>House Made Chorizo with Asturian Fabada wasnt bad. I love fabada beans so I enjoyed this very much.<br><br>Mushroom Canelones with Sherry Bechamel was very creamy and nice. It didn&#39;t taste too heavily of mushrooms which was great but you still felt that warm earthy taste.<br><br>Spanish Flan with Arrope Syrup was pretty delicious. Some bubbles in the flan but nice and thick and perfectly sweet. <br><br>Chocolate Cake with Espresso Whipped Cream. Nice thick chocolate cake. Wasnt frozen either. <br><br>I would definitely come back for the non-restaurant week menu.",
