"reviewcomment":"I would have given this reastaurant 5 stars, but sometimes the servers were too busy serving larger tables (I was alone) and they did not get to me when I needed something.   Other than that, the food was terrrific.  I was staying on Broadway, between 47th and 48th Streets, and this is walking distance from anywhere in Times Square. <br><br>I consider myself an oyster expert, since I live in the Puget Sound area and eat them a lot, mostly raw.  The oysters here were from NY and were exceptionally fresh.  The Pecan Encrusted Snapper (I am pretty sure it was Snapper, don&#39;t remember for sure) was very moist and tasted excellent.  I also ordered a spinach dish, it is a side so it serves more than one person.  It was also excellent.   <br><br>I was greeted when I came in by the Maitre D&#39;, and she was extremely friendly.  She took my Seahawks jacket and hat (I was in NY for Super Bowl XLVIII), gave me a claim chip, and she seated me.  I have her card, I will edit this post with her name for those who want to know, but I loved her attentiveness throughout my stay in her restaurant. It was definitely appreciated, and delightfully unusual based on my many restaurant experiences in &#34;upper level&#34; restaurants such as this one.   <br><br>Most guests were well dressed.  The staff were also well dressed.  The decor was very nice, with linen table cloths. Yet, when I came in dressed in jeans and a collared fleece sweater and Seahawks jacket and hat  (I looked clean and neat), they had no problem seating me.  <br><br> The servers are mostly Latino, and most have a thick accent.  I  am slightly hearing impaired, and they were difficult to understand with the background noise of the restaurant.  This is about my only complaint, but it is minor, besides the issue I stated at the outset of this review about sometimes being overlooked by them during the evening.  For the most part, however, they were extremely attentive.  I did have to bring to their attention that I had asked for a drink refill, and it never came, but they charged me for it anyway.  But they quickly removed the charge.  The server swept my table with a crumber after my meal, and I like that. <br><br>If you are looking for excellent seafood, look no farther than this restaurant if you are staying in, or visiting, Manhattan/Times Square area.",
