"reviewcomment":"Very romantic and classy. I can see why this place has a Michelin star. <br><br>As soon as you walk in, everyone is very attentive. The hostess took my coat right away and one of her colleagues showed me to the bar while I waited for the rest of my party to arrive. The waiter addressed my dining companion by name [I guess he was notified via the reservation? Kudos to the restaurant!] <br><br>Foie Gras [$24]: I shared this with my dinner mate even though I&#39;m really opposed to sharing. The foie was so silky smooth and creamy. The radicchio, being crunchy, was a nice texture contrast. The saba was acidic so it cut through the fat nicely. I would have liked to eat this dish on my own. <br><br>Dentice [$32]; The red snapper was served skin on and it was incredible. The meat was flakey and well seasoned and the crispy skin just added to the amazeballs. The lamb sausage on the side was fantastic, caught me off guard by how spicy it was. The brussels sprouts and celery just rounded out the dish. It&#39;s definitely better to eat all the components of this dish together than separate. <br><br>Bombolini [$11] Ahhhhh. Four Tuscan doughnuts covered in sugar and filled with a type of dulce de leche cream. A-maz-ing. Again, another shared dish, but this definitely had to be shared unless I wanted diabetes. The bittersweet chocolate was a bit of an overkill but still incredible. <br><br>Interestingly enough, when I asked where the restroom was, I was physically walked there. Also, my gloves were placed in a paper bag so they wouldn&#39;t get lost in the coat check room. <br><br>A little stuffy and formal, but its the small details that makes this place great.",
