"reviewcomment":"The semi-dark hallway leading to the reception was not only the introduction to an airy two spacious rooms overlooking Columbus Circle, but also was the beginning to a delightful interaction with a very welcoming, friendly and informative staff.<br><br>The extra virgin olive oil mixed with a hint of chili flakes, freshly ground black pepper and herbs was the invite into a promising prix-fixe three-course lunch menu, especially after the first bite of dipped fluffy focaccia bread was enjoyed.  The taste of the delicious oil carried over to the Crescione; a hearty watercress and frisee salad that was topped with thinly sliced pears.  Although the long, chunky cut of the watercress, together with its dripping the excess of dressing that remained in the bottom of the deep oval plate, took away a bit of the crisp greens&#39; charm, the sprinkled pantaleo goat cheese on the top of the crisp salad was nothing but a brilliant addition.<br><br>The arrival of the secondi course declared out loud the sleek modern look the interior carried was to be vividly witnessed throughout the presentation of the main course.  A grilled Dorade fish it was.  The freshness of the buttery fish, along with its crispy skin, started to isolate me from yet a very busy restaurant.  It was one of the two stars on the stage.  The bed of sautéed chickpea and tomatoes, mixed with kale chips and oil, announced the cuisine had not yet departed from its traditional Italian roots.  The full essence of the plate was captured, delightfully.  <br><br>As the spectacle was about to let its curtain down, the second of the two stars arrived: the Tiramisu.  The scene had a glossy chocolate doom covering a heavenly cream of espresso and mascarpone on a thin layer of almost-dry sponge cake, neighbored with an almond gelato placed on a dust of chocolate crumbs.  The contemporary presentation was another metaphor of not judging the book from its cover as the taste of Italy&#39;s traditional dessert--which I could not have enough of--proofed its originality despite its deceiving, yet beautiful, look.  Absolutely whimsical.  Enough Said!<br><br>(This review took place in a lunch visit on February 17th, 2014).",
