"reviewcomment":"Despite the Michelin star, it&#39;s still a treasure hunt to find good dishes (but there&#39;s treasure out there!)<br><br>Been here a few times for lunch already, and can&#39;t say I&#39;ve been disappointed. The flavors and spice of the dishes are on point. The most difficult part of the experience is choosing the right dishes!<br><br>When looking at the lunch specials menu, don&#39;t be led astray with Americanized choices (sesame chicken, beef with broccoli, etc). If you&#39;re feeling adventurous, ask for the full menu and your eyes will be opened. Some of my favorites include mapo tofu, fish and tofu in chili oil, and double cooked pork.<br><br>Another plus, lunch is less than $10, you get a soup with your entree, and it&#39;s lightning fast! If you&#39;re looking for some spice in your life, hop on over, sip your tea, and nom away!",
